You are an expert at generating photorealistic food photography prompts for AI image generation (Midjourney / DALL-E / Stable Diffusion).

Create **3 distinct image prompts** for the "Tea Pantry Staples: Building Your Tea Cuisine Kitchen" blog post.

## Image 1: Pantry Flat Lay
Style: Editorial still life photography, shallow depth of field
Subject: A beautifully arranged flat lay of tea-cuisine pantry staples on a dark wood table: five small bowls of different tea leaves (Keemun black, jasmine green, pu-erh, oolong, Lapsang Souchong) arranged in a circle, surrounded by rock sugar crystals, star anise pods, cinnamon sticks, dried tangerine peel, and small jars of light and dark soy sauce. A small square of cheesecloth folded beside a bamboo steamer basket.
Props: Ceramic bowls, glass spice jars, wooden chopsticks, cheesecloth, small bamboo steamer
Lighting: Soft, diffused natural daylight from the side, gentle shadows
Mood: Warm, inviting, organized, educational — like a cookbook spread
Composition: Overhead flat lay, symmetrical but with organic spacing, rich brown and amber tones dominating, shallow focus on the tea bowls

## Image 2: Tea Smoker Setup
Style: Documentary food photography, slightly warm color grade
Subject: A carbon steel wok on a gas stove with a tight-fitting lid slightly ajar, revealing a small pile of Lapsang Souchong leaves and star anise smoking in the bottom. Wisps of aromatic smoke curling upward. A metal steaming rack inside the wok holds a piece of chicken or tofu. A small spray bottle and extra tea leaves on the counter beside the stove.
Props: Carbon steel wok, glass lid, metal steaming rack, spray bottle, small ceramic bowl of extra tea leaves
Lighting: Warm overhead kitchen light mixed with cool window light, soft highlights on the smoke
Mood: Action-oriented, cozy, slightly dramatic — capturing the moment of tea-smoking in progress
Composition: Eye-level angle, wok filling the lower two-thirds of frame, smoke rising into the upper third, background softly blurred

## Image 3: Steamed Fish with Jasmine Tea
Style: Fine dining food photography, clean and bright
Subject: A whole steamed fish (or fillet) on a white plate, resting inside a bamboo steamer basket, garnished with delicate jasmine flowers and thin ginger slices. The basket sits above a shallow pool of jasmine-green-tea-infused steaming water visible through the bamboo slats. Steam rises gently around the plate.
Props: Bamboo steamer, white ceramic plate, jasmine flowers, ginger slices, scallion slivers, tea leaves scattered on the steamer base
Lighting: Bright, clean overhead studio light with soft fill from the front — bright white background
Mood: Pristine, elegant, fresh — like a restaurant presentation
Composition: Slightly elevated angle (45 degrees), centered subject, clean white or light grey background, steam adding movement and atmosphere
